Unknown gunmen, on Thursday, abducted two students of Calvary International Ministry, in Barkin Ladi Local Government Area of Plateau State. The school, which is popularly known as CAPRO, is situated a few kilometres from the Yakubu Gowon International Airport in Haipang. One of the two abducted students was, however, able to escape from the gunmen as security operatives engaged them. It was learnt that the gunmen came to the school in the early hours of Thursday in their numbers but as the security operatives were notified, they fled with the two students before one was able to escape. The Plateau State police commandâ€™s Public Relations Officer, Gabriel Ogaba, has confirmed the incident. However, the school management is yet to speak about the incident.